HEADWORD: Proin
<hw>Proin</hw> <pr>(proin)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Prune</er> to trim.]</ety> <def>To lop; to trim; to prune; to
adorn.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sprigs that did about it grow⟦br⟧
He <qex>proined</qex> from the leafy arms.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

